text: Sittingbourne and Milton was an urban district in Kent, England, consisting of the settlements of Sittingbourne and Milton Regis. It was abolished in 1974 under the Local Government Act 1972, and made part of the Swale district. ==References== Category:History of Kent Category:Districts of England abolished by the Local Government Act 1972 Category:Urban districts of England Category:Sittingbourne
title: Sittingbourne and Milton Urban District
